titles.title: A joint resolution approving the extension of nondiscriminatory treatment (most-favored-nation treatment) to the products of Romania.

action.text: Read twice and referred to the Committee on Finance.

calendar.text: Committee on Finance. Ordered to be reported without amendment favorably.

action.text: Committee on Finance. Reported to Senate by Senator Moynihan without amendment. With written report No. 103-159.

calendar.text: Placed on Senate Legislative Calendar under General Orders. Calendar No. 236.

action.text: Indefinitely postponed by Senate by Unanimous Consent.

bill.summary: 7/13/1993--Introduced. Approves the extension of nondiscriminatory treatment (most-favored-nation treatment) to the products of Romania pursuant to the message transmitted to the Congress by the President on July 13, 1993.
